EXTRACTED VALUE: The Corolla is available in Base, S, LE, XLE and sporty XRS trim levels. Competitors include the Chevrolet Cobalt, Ford Focus, Mazda3 and Honda Civic.
The Kizashi is Suzuki's entry in the ultra-competitive midsize sedan market. Its name means "something great is coming" in Japanese.
The midsize Galant sedan is now offered only with four-cylinder power. It competes with the Chevrolet Malibu, Honda Accord and Toyota Camry.
The high-end Cadillac Escalade EXT sport utility truck competes with fully loaded pickups like the Toyota Tundra Limited and Ford F-150 Platinum.
The Eos is a four-seat hardtop convertible, and it occupies a small niche in the car market. It's sold in Komfort and Lux trim levels.
The Lancer competes against other small sedans like the Ford Focus, Honda Civic and Mazda3, and there's a high-performance Ralliart trim level.
The Caliber is a five-seat, four-door hatchback. The Caliber comes in Express, Mainstreet, Uptown, Heat and Rush trim levels.
Acura's entry-level TSX sport sedan was redesigned for 2009. Its competitors include the Audi A4, BMW 328i and Lexus IS 250.
